<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="111" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1105,1493]" pageId="5" pageNumber="111">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,289,1105,1131]" pageId="5" pageNumber="111">Description</emphasis>
. Head in frontal view oval; frontal ridge narrow, almost reaching the clypeus. Face in lateral view reclinated; frontal ridge considerably projecting between the antennae and forming a widened rostrum (
<figureCitation box="[1267,1332,1142,1168]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–14" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1796,1820]" captionTargetBox="[218,1367,192,1763]" captionTargetId="figure-15@6.[211,1377,181,1772]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 1–14. Subfamily Incolacridinae. 1. Bettotania cincifemur, female body, lateral view (schematic after Miller, 1935); 2. Stolzia rubromaculata, male head and pronotum, lateral view (schematic after C. Willemse, 1930); 3. Stolzia javana, female head, frontal view; 4–7. Incolacris rubritarsi, female: 4. Head and pronotum, lateral view; 5. Head, frontal view; 6. Apex of abdomen, lateral view (after Hollis, 1975); 7. The same, ventral view (after Hollis, 1975); 8–12. Incolacris jianfengensis comb. nov., male (after Zheng &amp; Ma, 1989): 8. Head and pronotum, lateral view; 9. The same, dorsal view; 10. Apex of abdomen, dorsal view; 11. The same, lateral view; 12. Hind knee, lateral view; 13. Asymmetritania asymmetrica comb. nov., male apex of abdomen, dorsal view (after Ingrisch, 1989); 14. Asymmetritania vietnamensis comb. nov., male hind knee, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756021" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756021/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="111">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Ventral genicular lobes of the hind femora narrowly triangular with apex obtuse, without spine. Male 10th abdominal tergite with furculae. Male supra-anal plate long-oval, with a median basal impression, lateral margins with a pointed tooth somewhat behind the middle, apex rounded. Male cerci compressed, conical, apex pointed, inner side without tooth. Valves of ovipositor relatively long, with apex rounded and crenulate (
<figureCitation box="[957,1024,1286,1312]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–14" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1796,1820]" captionTargetBox="[218,1367,192,1763]" captionTargetId="figure-15@6.[211,1377,181,1772]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 1–14. Subfamily Incolacridinae. 1. Bettotania cincifemur, female body, lateral view (schematic after Miller, 1935); 2. Stolzia rubromaculata, male head and pronotum, lateral view (schematic after C. Willemse, 1930); 3. Stolzia javana, female head, frontal view; 4–7. Incolacris rubritarsi, female: 4. Head and pronotum, lateral view; 5. Head, frontal view; 6. Apex of abdomen, lateral view (after Hollis, 1975); 7. The same, ventral view (after Hollis, 1975); 8–12. Incolacris jianfengensis comb. nov., male (after Zheng &amp; Ma, 1989): 8. Head and pronotum, lateral view; 9. The same, dorsal view; 10. Apex of abdomen, dorsal view; 11. The same, lateral view; 12. Hind knee, lateral view; 13. Asymmetritania asymmetrica comb. nov., male apex of abdomen, dorsal view (after Ingrisch, 1989); 14. Asymmetritania vietnamensis comb. nov., male hind knee, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756021" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756021/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="111">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Male genitalia: epiphallus divided and asymmetrical; bridge relatively broad; left lophus long, finger-shaped; right lophus small, rounded; ancorae absent; oval sclerites attached to epiphallus (
<figureCitation box="[661,746,1358,1384]" captionStart="FIGURES 15–24" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1734,1758]" captionTargetBox="[160,1424,316,1701]" captionTargetId="figure-80@8.[151,1436,308,1710]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 15–24. Male genitalia of the subfamily Incolacridinae (15–18 after Hollis, 1975 and 19–24 after Ingrisch, 1989). 15. Incolacris trifasciata, epiphallus, dorsal view; 16. The same, Stolzia javana; 17. The same, Stolzia aberrans; 18. The same, Stolzia fasciata; 19–21. Bettotania maculata: 19. Epiphallus, dorsal view; 20. Phallic complex (epiphallus removed), dorsal view; 21. The same, lateral view; 22–24. Asymmetritania asymmetrica comb. nov.: 22. Epiphallus, dorsal view; 23. Phallic complex (epiphallus removed), lateral view; 24. The same, dorsal view. (Ae—ancorae; An—anterior projections of epiphallus; Ap—apical valves of penis; Apd—apodemes; Bp—basal valves of penis; Br—bridge; Cv—valves of cingulum; Fx—flexure; Lel—left lophi of epiphallus; Ler—right lophi of epiphallus; Os—oval sclerites; Rm—rami of cingulum; Sh—ectophallic sheath of penis; Zyg—zygoma)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756023" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756023/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="111">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
); apodemes broad; valves of cingulum short; basal valves of penis connected with apical ones by a sinuate, long, unbroken flexure (
<figureCitation box="[930,1012,1394,1420]" captionStart="FIGURES 15–24" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1734,1758]" captionTargetBox="[160,1424,316,1701]" captionTargetId="figure-80@8.[151,1436,308,1710]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 15–24. Male genitalia of the subfamily Incolacridinae (15–18 after Hollis, 1975 and 19–24 after Ingrisch, 1989). 15. Incolacris trifasciata, epiphallus, dorsal view; 16. The same, Stolzia javana; 17. The same, Stolzia aberrans; 18. The same, Stolzia fasciata; 19–21. Bettotania maculata: 19. Epiphallus, dorsal view; 20. Phallic complex (epiphallus removed), dorsal view; 21. The same, lateral view; 22–24. Asymmetritania asymmetrica comb. nov.: 22. Epiphallus, dorsal view; 23. Phallic complex (epiphallus removed), lateral view; 24. The same, dorsal view. (Ae—ancorae; An—anterior projections of epiphallus; Ap—apical valves of penis; Apd—apodemes; Bp—basal valves of penis; Br—bridge; Cv—valves of cingulum; Fx—flexure; Lel—left lophi of epiphallus; Ler—right lophi of epiphallus; Os—oval sclerites; Rm—rami of cingulum; Sh—ectophallic sheath of penis; Zyg—zygoma)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4756023" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4756023/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="111">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1105,1493]" pageId="5" pageNumber="111">
